Sugar Traders, Exchange Discuss ‘Circuit Breakers,’ FT Reports

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-02-23T02:34:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/sugar-traders-exchange-discuss-circuit-breakers-ft-reports.html
The ICE Futures U.S. Exchange and
the World Sugar Committee are considering introducing so-called
“circuit breakers” to curb volatility in sugar prices, the
Financial Times reported, citing unidentified people familiar
with the discussions. The system, used in equity and other  commodities markets , interrupts trading when prices move beyond
a certain limit, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 